http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/human-Animal-conflict/article13999181.ece

A 10-ft.-long python created a flutter in AP Model School at Gudupalle close to the Dravidian University in Kuppam on Wednesday. It was killed by local farmers.A special class was under way for Class X students in one corner of the room when the python crawled towards the benches.Spotting the reptile, the students ran helter-skelter, drawing the attention of farmers working in the fields nearby. They rushed to the classroom and killed the snake.In another incident, a spotted deer strayed into the human habitation in Kuppam town from the Maharaja Kadai forests in Tamil Nadu. On being informed by the residents, the forest officials caught the animal and released it in deep forests.